casebody.data:
Jim Herrin Pontiac, Inc. et al., Appellants, v. Heintschell, Appellee.

[Cite as Jim Herrin Pontiac, Inc. v. Heintschell (1991), 57 Ohio St. 3d 602.]

(No. 89-1983 Submitted November 27, 1990 Decided January 2, 1991.) Schnorf, Schnorf & Ballard, David M. Schnorf and Christopher F. Parker, for appellants. Oxley, Malone, Fitzgerald & Hollister, Robert B. Hollister and Julie A. Davenport, for appellee.

The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

The court orders that the court of appeals’ opinion not be published in the Ohio Official Reports.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
